<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Kiichiro Wakayama] </F>
  [Text] Shanghai, 15 Jan -- According to a Chinese source, 
China's supreme leader Deng Xiaoping, who is staying in 
Shanghai, will visit Guangzhou and Zhuhai in Guangdong Province 
between late January and Chinese New Year's day (10 February). 
Moreover, the possibility of a visit to Hainan Province is also 
being studied. In recent years, Mr. Deng has spent New Year's 
days in Shanghai. However, he will leave Shanghai this year. 
  The inspection tour to the southern region is aimed at 
showing Mr. Deng's strong will regarding the complicated Hong 
Kong issue by visiting Guangdong Province, which has close 
economic ties with Hong Kong. At the same time, it seems the 
visit is also aimed at seeking continuation of high level 
economic growth in southern China. 

