<F P=100> North Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hebei's Xingtai City Opens New Flights to Jiangsu </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2801082694 Shijiazhuang Hebei People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2801082694 </F>
<F P=104>  Shijiazhuang Hebei People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to our station reporter's dispatch from 
the press conference sponsored by Xingtai City Lianhe Airline on 
26 January, the Xingtai airport will open new flights to the 
cities of Suzhou and Wuxi of Jiangsu Province on 23 February. 
These new flights will establish a bridge between Xingtai and 
the middle and lower reaches of the Chang Jiang. The opening of 
new flights will exert active influence on broadening the 
economic, cultural, and technical exchanges among different 
regions and on improving the investment environment of south 
Hebei. 

</TEXT>

